WEBVTT

00:19.750 --> 00:21.020
The wind?

00:24.500 --> 00:25.780
Are you awake?

00:27.960 --> 00:30.760
I hailed us a Pegasus Carriage.

00:30.760 --> 00:31.760
Huh?

00:32.440 --> 00:35.140
Flying so high must've 
been cold in your pajamas.

00:35.610 --> 00:37.250
We're almost there.

00:39.690 --> 00:41.890
There, can you see it?

00:52.140 --> 00:56.000
That's my atelier and 
the school you'll be learning at.

02:28.540 --> 02:34.380
<b>The School of the Grassland</b>

02:31.980 --> 02:36.010
I planted Guard Briar seeds 
around your house.

02:36.590 --> 02:40.400
They'll grow in no time 
and act as a barrier.

02:40.800 --> 02:44.640
Your house was petrified 
by an unknown spell,

02:45.520 --> 02:48.520
so it'll keep people 
from getting too close to it.

02:54.440 --> 02:55.610
So...

02:57.310 --> 02:58.310
Coco?

03:03.510 --> 03:04.680
What's the matter?

03:05.540 --> 03:10.240
I promised my mom I wouldn't 
leave her by herself.

03:10.240 --> 03:11.320
But I...

03:12.280 --> 03:13.330
Coco...

03:18.550 --> 03:22.400
Don't be hard on yourself. 
You didn't know what you were doing.

03:35.280 --> 03:37.400
Here, let's wash your face.

03:37.880 --> 03:40.970
Let all your tears out, then look ahead.

03:43.590 --> 03:45.920
Because this is going to 
be your new home starting today.

03:56.840 --> 03:59.150
Um, what is this?

03:59.150 --> 04:01.480
Hmm? Water, of course.

04:04.460 --> 04:08.770
Ah. I totally forgot! 
You need a change of clothes.

04:05.190 --> 04:08.770
<i>It feels too round and floaty 
to be called water.</i>

04:09.650 --> 04:10.650
Huh?

04:11.010 --> 04:13.650
How am I supposed to use this?

04:14.380 --> 04:15.790
Mister Qifrey?

04:18.330 --> 04:21.910
I'm scared of touching 
magic I don't understand.

04:21.910 --> 04:23.870
There's nothing to be afraid of!

04:24.270 --> 04:26.870
It's not a difficult 
kind of magic to handle.

04:29.460 --> 04:31.800
Want me to teach you?

04:35.000 --> 04:37.520
That's a Vapor Bubble.

04:37.890 --> 04:41.460
It's magic that pulls water 
out of the moisture in the air.

04:41.820 --> 04:44.510
Here, hold out your hands.

04:45.630 --> 04:49.280
Tilt the lower tray, 
and the water pours out.

04:49.770 --> 04:53.390
Wow, that's amazing. Thank you.

04:53.390 --> 04:54.900
Thank you!

04:54.900 --> 04:55.650
Huh?

04:55.650 --> 04:58.890
I love being told "Thank you."

04:58.890 --> 05:00.780
So thank you!

05:01.230 --> 05:04.420
Oh, um... I see.

05:04.420 --> 05:05.810
Thanks.

05:05.810 --> 05:08.580
Thank <i>you</i> for thanking me again!

05:08.580 --> 05:12.210
Thank you for thanking me, 
and thank you again...

05:12.210 --> 05:14.460
Just ignore her if she's too much.

05:16.380 --> 05:18.880
She'll stop eventually if you 
just don't respond.

05:19.340 --> 05:24.420
How mean, Richeh! I was just helping her.

05:26.480 --> 05:28.180
The pen and ink.

05:29.460 --> 05:31.590
Are you both witches?

05:31.590 --> 05:35.810
Just apprentices. 
We're students of Master Qifrey.

05:35.810 --> 05:38.320
Wait, so you're not?

05:38.800 --> 05:42.300
I totally thought you were 
a fellow student like us.

05:42.300 --> 05:45.130
Are we the same age? 
Which atelier did you come from?

05:45.130 --> 05:46.830
Uh...

05:47.640 --> 05:50.700
I don't think I can call myself 
a student just yet.

05:50.700 --> 05:54.610
I mean, yesterday was 
the first time I ever drew a spell.

05:55.060 --> 05:57.340
But I'm going to live here as of today.

05:58.920 --> 05:59.940
What?

06:01.150 --> 06:02.150
Huh?

06:02.590 --> 06:05.840
Wait, so you're the one who did it?

06:06.130 --> 06:08.100
Did what?

06:15.900 --> 06:17.680
There's a rumor going around

06:18.950 --> 06:22.480
about an Outsider who used 
forbidden magic...

06:22.480 --> 06:26.080
That they were allowed to become an 
apprentice with their memories intact...

06:28.240 --> 06:29.250
Coco.

06:31.110 --> 06:32.400
Are you okay?

06:32.400 --> 06:33.830
Mr. Qifrey...

06:34.370 --> 06:37.380
Looks like you all introduced yourselves.

06:37.380 --> 06:40.190
Richeh and Tetia, 
will you go study in your rooms

06:40.190 --> 06:42.080
after helping with the morning chores?

06:42.080 --> 06:43.500
Okay!

06:44.440 --> 06:47.640
Here are your new clothes. 
This is what my students wear.

06:50.390 --> 06:53.600
Don't be afraid. I'll explain everything.

06:56.270 --> 06:57.920
Looks like it fits you perfectly.

07:00.440 --> 07:04.030
Now then, let us begin 
the story of magic.

07:07.390 --> 07:12.090
Long ago, magic wasn't something special.

07:13.410 --> 07:17.920
All you needed was a combination of 
known patterns and specially made ink.

07:23.690 --> 07:28.330
It was a familiar tool 
that anyone could use.

07:30.140 --> 07:34.510
However, it sparked conflict 
time and time again.

07:36.790 --> 07:38.960
When humans are given 
the power to do anything,

07:38.960 --> 07:40.870
"anything" is what they will do.

07:41.540 --> 07:44.390
And so, many horrific spells were created.

07:49.040 --> 07:51.890
The few people who still had a conscience

07:51.890 --> 07:55.860
turned away from conflict 
and unified as witches

07:55.860 --> 07:58.490
to take other people's memories of magic,

07:58.490 --> 08:02.810
entrusting the secret only to 
disciples sworn to protect it.

08:03.930 --> 08:06.160
That was the Day of the Pact.

08:07.000 --> 08:09.630
Ever since then, 
people have been made to believe

08:09.630 --> 08:12.110
that magic is a power only 
a chosen few can wield.

08:12.550 --> 08:14.750
If the truth were to spread,

08:14.750 --> 08:17.390
the world would collapse 
into lawlessness once again.

08:17.880 --> 08:21.410
Everyone's being careful 
to keep the secret.

08:21.780 --> 08:23.900
That's why they started 
talking about you.

08:24.240 --> 08:25.430
I'm sorry you had to hear that.

08:25.900 --> 08:29.150
No, I brought this on myself.

08:29.950 --> 08:33.160
Um, what's "forbidden magic"?

08:34.530 --> 08:36.820
Magic that was drawn 
during the age of conflict

08:36.820 --> 08:39.320
and banned when the Day of the Pact came—

08:40.290 --> 08:42.290
magic for hurting others.

08:44.800 --> 08:46.790
Please teach me!

08:46.790 --> 08:48.920
Teach me all about the magic 
that I'm not supposed to use!

08:49.180 --> 08:50.220
I want to know!

08:51.840 --> 08:55.620
I'll be too scared to do anything 
if I don't know what it is.

08:57.830 --> 09:00.270
This is where I usually tell 
my students not to rush things,

09:00.710 --> 09:02.730
but that's harder with you.

09:05.250 --> 09:06.410
Come with me.

09:11.430 --> 09:14.660
There are countless forbidden spells,

09:14.660 --> 09:17.760
but it's simple when you boil it down.

09:18.570 --> 09:20.810
Any spell cast directly upon 
the human body

09:20.810 --> 09:22.900
is prohibited under all circumstances.

09:23.490 --> 09:26.820
This includes transformation, 
age alteration,

09:26.820 --> 09:29.830
teleportation without 
doors or conveyances,

09:30.560 --> 09:32.900
as well as the manipulation 
of thoughts or emotion,

09:32.900 --> 09:35.390
the harming of others, 
or even healing them.

09:36.150 --> 09:38.390
There is, however, a single exception.

09:39.050 --> 09:41.140
Erasing memories?

09:41.140 --> 09:42.560
Exactly.

09:44.820 --> 09:47.260
Most spells are cast on tools.

09:48.730 --> 09:50.830
Like carriages or lamps.

09:58.160 --> 10:01.500
Or windows like this one.

10:21.180 --> 10:22.670
A lake?!

10:23.640 --> 10:26.460
But we were surrounded 
by hills just a minute ago.

10:27.020 --> 10:28.790
It's called a Windowway.

10:28.790 --> 10:31.510
It connects two round windows 
that bear the same pattern.

10:32.820 --> 10:34.780
Can you see that building over there?

10:35.700 --> 10:37.000
That's the Tower of Tomes.

10:37.380 --> 10:41.320
To preserve knowledge, 
all books related to magic

10:41.320 --> 10:44.040
are duplicated there 
the moment they're written.

10:45.040 --> 10:46.660
The picture book...

10:47.140 --> 10:50.240
Let's go there right now! 
I won't sleep until I find it!

10:50.240 --> 10:51.050
Hold your horses.

11:08.910 --> 11:10.730
That was the Librarians' Trial.

11:11.210 --> 11:14.470
The Tower of Tomes 
is protected by four librarians,

11:14.470 --> 11:18.110
and only witches who overcome it 
are allowed to enter.

11:18.890 --> 11:21.950
So you need to study 
if you want to go inside.

11:23.040 --> 11:23.950
Coco.

11:24.570 --> 11:29.080
It made me happy earlier when you 
expressed how eager you are to learn.

11:29.990 --> 11:32.090
It's natural to feel fear.

11:32.420 --> 11:33.440
But...

11:35.010 --> 11:37.840
The spells that are not forbidden

11:42.740 --> 11:45.750
are those that bring 
happiness to all of us.

11:47.150 --> 11:50.610
So why not learn about 
the gentler sort of spell?

11:51.730 --> 11:52.750
That's how I feel.

11:53.910 --> 11:55.050
What do you say?

11:56.190 --> 11:58.820
Yes. Of course, Master Qifrey.

12:02.900 --> 12:04.540
This'll be your room.

12:08.000 --> 12:09.870
Looks like Agott's not around.

12:09.870 --> 12:11.420
Who's Agott?

12:11.420 --> 12:13.290
Your roommate.

12:19.250 --> 12:21.910
The two of you will share a workspace.

12:21.910 --> 12:23.680
You'll have your own bedroom, though.

12:26.120 --> 12:29.970
Go down the stairs in the back. 
Don't worry, the doors can be locked.

12:31.190 --> 12:33.060
You should get some rest.

12:33.460 --> 12:36.580
I have some things to take care of, 
so call if you need anything.

12:47.520 --> 12:49.530
It's me, Qifrey.

12:50.090 --> 12:53.790
Thank you for allowing me 
to take in Coco as my apprentice.

12:55.100 --> 12:59.840
Yes. No, nothing about the picture book.

12:59.840 --> 13:02.300
She's overwhelmed right now.

13:04.930 --> 13:07.860
So this is what a witch's room looks like?

13:09.310 --> 13:11.690
That's my side of the desk.

13:23.320 --> 13:25.950
Move so I can land.

13:25.950 --> 13:27.870
Oh, sorry.

13:38.640 --> 13:41.060
You're Agott, right? I'm Coco—

13:41.060 --> 13:42.070
I know who you are.

13:42.640 --> 13:44.700
You're the Outsider 
everyone's talking about.

13:45.120 --> 13:48.120
I heard you'll be joining as a new peer.

13:49.310 --> 13:51.940
I'm sorry about your mother.

13:52.730 --> 13:54.810
Th-Thanks.

13:54.810 --> 13:56.770
Because of what you've done,

13:59.110 --> 14:01.780
she'll never return to being human.

14:03.280 --> 14:05.790
I came here to save her.

14:06.520 --> 14:07.780
By becoming a witch—

14:10.370 --> 14:13.520
Our whole lives, we've been 
drawing Casting Seals

14:13.520 --> 14:15.070
until our fingertips turned black.

14:15.070 --> 14:17.530
We worked and worked 
until we passed the tests,

14:17.530 --> 14:20.340
and were only then allowed to 
become apprentices.

14:20.860 --> 14:23.240
You're an ordinary girl who knows nothing.

14:23.240 --> 14:26.600
There's no way an Outsider such as 
yourself can become a witch.

14:29.910 --> 14:33.000
I... I've drawn spells already!

14:33.530 --> 14:35.230
I won't know until I try it!

14:35.230 --> 14:37.440
Then prove yourself.

14:37.440 --> 14:38.620
Your tests start tomorrow—

14:38.620 --> 14:40.820
Agott! Coco!

14:40.820 --> 14:42.900
Food is ready!

14:43.320 --> 14:45.020
Let's eat!

14:50.950 --> 14:52.550
I'm starving.

14:52.550 --> 14:57.140
Me, too! We're having 
Coco's welcome party today!

14:57.140 --> 14:58.670
Lots of food.

15:06.700 --> 15:08.410
Same as usual.

15:09.230 --> 15:11.810
Master, what happened 
to the welcome party?

15:12.100 --> 15:15.740
It was so last-minute. 
We'll do it another time.

15:16.120 --> 15:17.320
Where's Agott?

15:17.320 --> 15:19.130
She said she's eating in her room.

15:19.780 --> 15:23.200
She should join us once in a while.

15:23.600 --> 15:25.850
Okay, let's eat.

15:26.320 --> 15:29.360
Would you do the honors, Coco?

15:29.360 --> 15:31.150
Huh? Uh, sure.

15:32.350 --> 15:33.940
Let's eat.

15:33.940 --> 15:35.580
Let's eat.

15:43.110 --> 15:44.360
It's so good.

15:44.360 --> 15:47.600
I know, right? We bake it ourselves.

15:47.980 --> 15:49.830
Master is a great chef.

15:49.830 --> 15:50.970
That's amazing.

15:51.490 --> 15:53.970
It's thanks to the locally grown wheat.

16:02.700 --> 16:05.750
We get great veggies around here.

16:06.320 --> 16:08.250
Thank you for the food.

16:33.320 --> 16:34.820
Mom...

16:44.290 --> 16:48.300
I need to take tests in order 
to become an apprentice.

16:49.250 --> 16:54.470
But it doesn't go into detail 
about what you need to do.

16:54.470 --> 16:56.080
Need to do about what?

16:58.470 --> 17:01.850
There are lots of things books 
don't tell you when it comes to magic.

17:01.850 --> 17:05.380
You'll learn more 
from doing than from reading.

17:05.830 --> 17:07.010
What are these?

17:07.330 --> 17:10.650
Your Components—
tools used to draw magic.

17:11.760 --> 17:13.760
Wow!

17:14.020 --> 17:16.600
They look so cool!

17:18.610 --> 17:21.390
The Ink Wand. A pen.

17:22.450 --> 17:25.650
I still feel a bit scared 
touching this. But...

17:26.340 --> 17:29.500
<i>Mom, I'm going to save you 
no matter what it takes!</i>

17:30.270 --> 17:32.910
Master Qifrey, I look 
forward to our lessons.

17:32.910 --> 17:35.040
Okay, let's get started.

17:42.170 --> 17:45.240
Are you okay, Coco? 
Shall we take a break?

17:46.070 --> 17:48.250
I-I'm fine.

17:49.660 --> 17:53.010
Okay, try explaining to me 
what you learned.

17:53.010 --> 17:54.690
O-Okay.

17:55.180 --> 18:00.040
Um... A spell is composed 
of three elements.

18:00.700 --> 18:02.820
The sigil is in the center.

18:02.820 --> 18:06.410
It's surrounded by lines 
that are called signs.

18:06.410 --> 18:10.030
The outer circle that 
completes it is called the ring.

18:10.030 --> 18:12.430
The types of sigil—fire,

18:13.590 --> 18:14.550
water,

18:15.240 --> 18:16.420
light,

18:17.440 --> 18:18.560
and wind.

18:18.560 --> 18:21.660
They determine what kind
of magic it becomes.

18:22.120 --> 18:25.330
The signs determine 
what form the magic takes,

18:25.330 --> 18:27.920
as well as its size and direction.

18:28.750 --> 18:31.940
Lastly, when the outer ring is completed,

18:31.940 --> 18:35.160
that locks the seal in place
and activates the spell.

18:36.430 --> 18:39.950
I'm barely keeping up 
just memorizing everything.

18:39.950 --> 18:41.680
But you were able to explain it!

18:43.940 --> 18:45.930
I'm going to try drawing one!

18:45.930 --> 18:48.000
I like it! That's the spirit.

19:01.350 --> 19:02.300
Huh?

19:04.210 --> 19:06.210
Don't throw it away.

19:07.210 --> 19:08.960
No! Please don't look at it!

19:08.960 --> 19:11.430
It's not something I can show you!

19:11.430 --> 19:15.460
It's sloppy, and the lines 
are all wobbly and messy...

19:15.840 --> 19:19.080
Of course it is. You're just learning.

19:19.080 --> 19:22.350
But there's something else you 
should pay attention to.

19:22.750 --> 19:25.730
Look right here. 
See how your ring is not connected?

19:25.980 --> 19:28.770
A spell won't activate 
unless it's a complete circle.

19:32.230 --> 19:35.760
It's natural to have unsteady hands when 
you're learning to use a new tool.

19:35.760 --> 19:38.620
You're like a newborn 
foal just learning to stand.

19:38.900 --> 19:42.530
You'll get used to it and be 
running around freely in no time.

19:44.370 --> 19:47.890
Now, connect the lines 
and activate the spell.

20:02.570 --> 20:05.230
I-I'm sorry! Very sorry! 
It was an accident!

20:08.230 --> 20:11.230
Sorry! I'll dry it! I'll dry it off!

20:12.520 --> 20:14.340
Calm down, Coco!

20:12.520 --> 20:13.710
Has it dried?!

20:14.340 --> 20:16.380
Sorry, Agott. Are you okay?

20:15.830 --> 20:16.990
Not yet?!

20:18.450 --> 20:22.870
It's fine, Master. 
I'm not bothered by it at all.

20:23.140 --> 20:26.440
But may I see the Casting Seal she drew?

20:26.440 --> 20:28.370
Huh? Sure.

20:29.420 --> 20:31.630
Ah, I found the problem.

20:36.120 --> 20:37.010
Look.

20:38.090 --> 20:40.530
This sign is longer than the rest.

20:40.530 --> 20:45.390
It amplified pressure in this direction
and caused the water to gush out.

20:45.740 --> 20:48.930
As always, your observation 
is on point, Agott.

20:51.400 --> 20:53.650
I think I can leave her in your care.

20:53.650 --> 20:54.610
Huh?

20:59.860 --> 21:04.070
For the next two or three days, 
I'll be out visiting the Great Hall.

21:04.070 --> 21:07.620
Please look after her 
while I'm gone, Agott.

21:08.030 --> 21:09.900
Absolutely, Master.

21:11.000 --> 21:12.510
Wait!

21:12.510 --> 21:14.930
There's a lot you can learn 
from your peers.

21:14.930 --> 21:17.660
Watch her closely and learn, Coco.

21:19.200 --> 21:21.410
M-Master...

21:25.250 --> 21:28.580
Um, I'm really sorry about that. I—

21:28.580 --> 21:30.490
You don't have to keep apologizing.

21:30.490 --> 21:32.400
I said I wasn't bothered by it, didn't I?

21:33.540 --> 21:35.270
Now then, Coco.

21:36.500 --> 21:39.970
Yesterday, I told you to prove yourself.

21:40.580 --> 21:43.700
No more cushy little lessons.

21:44.180 --> 21:46.310
Your tests start now.

21:47.120 --> 21:48.260
What?

23:35.390 --> 23:39.980
Episode 3:

23:35.390 --> 23:39.980
The Dadah Range Test
